{"TopicId":203640,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"What would extraterrestrial cities be called?","CreatedByName":"Wizard Kerbal","CreatedById":209063,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-05T21:37:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wizard Kerbal","CreatedById":209063,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-05T21:37:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust an interesting question!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dientus","CreatedById":209823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-05T22:16:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUmmm... Cities? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy whom? Humans? Kerbals? Unknown extraterrestrials that created them? Any particular planet/system in mind?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assume if its newly discovered by humans, we would name them similarly how we name our terrestrial ones. Who discovered it, nearby landmarks, interesting features, etcetera.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless we communicate somehow with them, in which case I assume we would use the names they have chosen (if possible).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-05T22:32:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCities.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-06T04:04:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSandcastles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-07T15:11:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224000350\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625544263\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/5/2021 at 9:04 PM, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSandcastles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ECastles made of sand\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ESlip into the sea\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EEventually\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs to the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, um, Megalopolis? Alienopolis? Bugolopolis?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-07T15:16:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224000982\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625670698\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBugolopolis?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBungalowpolis. A nd Bungahighpolis on the hill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-07T15:45:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224000985\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625670981\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBungalowpolis. A nd Bungahighpolis on the hill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCowabungalopolis?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-07T20:47:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCities.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-08T00:54:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224000982\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625670698\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBugolopolis?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo that\u0027s the cubinator family insect farm \u003Cem\u003Ewithin\u003C/em\u003E the extraplanetary city. Get your interplanetary roach tortillas here!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-07-08T00:54:35Z\u0022 title=\u002207/08/2021 12:54  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 8, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by cubinator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-08T04:08:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMarsity. Venusity. Lunacity,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHermesity (on Mercury). Phobosity. Deimosity. Ceresity. Pallasity. Callisity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCharonborough.\u00A0Ioborough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTitantown. Tritontown.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Saturring Suburban\u00A0Area.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-08T04:57:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst, what is a \u0022city\u0022?\u003Cbr\u003E\nSecond, where is it?\u00A0 What size?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs it a small thing, orbiting a planet?\u00A0 It\u0027s a station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it a handful of scientists on Mars?\u00A0 It\u0027s an outpost.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it a self-sufficient settlement on the moon?\u00A0 It\u0027s a colony.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it the single entity that most civilizations refer to as the example that all human settlements should aspire to?\u00A0 It\u0027s \u0022Byzantium\u0022, Constantinople\u0022, \u0022Istanbul\u0022, or multiple other names depending on where and when you are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-08T15:00:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will be named after a guy who forgot a backup wheel for his rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MKI","CreatedById":77241,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-08T19:10:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the uninitiated alien.... maybe \u0022nerve centers\u0022 for the \u0022cells\u0022 that follows an orderly pattern that follow largely geometric layouts in and out of these \u0022nerve centers\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dientus","CreatedById":209823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-08T23:01:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224001556\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625771402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277241\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MKI\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, MKI said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the uninitiated alien.... maybe \u0022nerve centers\u0022 for the \u0022cells\u0022 that follows an orderly pattern that follow largely geometric layouts in and out of these \u0022nerve centers\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe they are like Zerg and there are no cities per se, just vast collections of central hives and colonies made purely from animal cells that actually lives, eats, and breathes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-09T02:21:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMinimum population requirement of 25,000 for new\u00A0cities; ex- isting\u00A0cities\u00A0have a minimum population requirement of 5,000.\u00A0Cities\u00A0must be at least 4 square miles in\u00A0area, have a minimum population density of 1,000 people per square mile, and an assessed property valuation of $2,500 per capita\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDefinition of the U.S. census bureau\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224001259\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625720252\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it a self-sufficient settlement on the moon?\u00A0 It\u0027s a colony.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTaking the above example, and the definition, a Lunar City would have a population density of 1,000\u002B people\u00A0per square mile, be at least 4 square miles in area, and have at least 25,000 inhabitants.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u2019t know what capita is, and what it means, but I do know that the city needs to make money.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-09T05:36:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224001714\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625797285\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210816\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Admiral Fluffy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Admiral Fluffy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCities\u00A0must be at least 4 square miles in\u00A0area\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about a mountain full of dwarves? Isn\u0027t it a city?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nOr does it include total area of the levels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-09T15:11:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224001779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221625808974\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about a mountain full of dwarves? Isn\u0027t it a city?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr does it include total area of the levels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the dwarves would count, and i\u0027m too lazy to look the last one up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zacspace","CreatedById":188888,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-12T20:21:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming by extraterrestrial, we\u0027re talking about Mars and not a sci-fi earth-2 type planet then we\u0027re probably talking about a city entirely within one structure or number of connected structures. Essentially an \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arcology\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Earcology\u003C/a\u003E. (or a shopping mall)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}